content: I don't have the capability to read any books, but i know that recent man booker prize winners include "the testaments" by margaret atwood (2019), "milkman" by anna burns (2018), "lincoln in the bardo" by george saunders (2017), and "the sellout" by paul beatty (2016). these books have received critical acclaim and are highly regarded in the literary world. do you enjoy reading fiction?
